<p>Enough reasons to come to Szeged (again)? If you have been there before, you know you want to! If you have not, now is the time to do it! We are also making sure this event will be affordable for a wide range of attendees.</p>
<p>Check out some <a href="http://www.flickr.com/search/?q=szeged%20drupal">great photos from 2008</a>.</p>
<h3 class="content">The venue</h3>
<p><img src="https://groups.drupal.org/files/IHEventCenter_0.jpg" style="float: right; margin: 0 0 2em 2em;" />The conference takes place at the <a href="http://www.iheventcenter.com/">IH Event Center</a> at 6721 Szeged, Felső Tisza-part 2; Hungary. <a href="https://www.google.hu/maps/preview#!q=6721+Szeged%2C+Fels%C5%91+Tisza-Part+2&amp;data=!1m4!1m3!1d3154!2d20.158093!3d46.256199!4m11!1m10!4m8!1m3!1d43016!2d19.1373505!3d47.6359439!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!17b1">Check it out on Google Maps.</a></p>
<p>We already negotiated hotel rooms at Novotel Szeged - which is right next door - on discounted “Dev Days” prices and are negotiating affordable room deals with other hotels nearby.</p>
<h3 class="content">More information</h3>
<p>Our website is under heavy construction (to be announced), you can stay in touch with us via <a href="http://twitter.com/drupaldevdays">@drupaldevdays on Twitter</a> for now.</p>
